#: en/drawing.html+html.body.p:10
msgid ""
"When you are working in the <i>Animation module</i>, you will have the "
"<i>pencil</i> automatically selected as the tool at your disposal in the "
"first frame of animation."
msgstr ""

#: en/drawing.html+html.body.center.p:18
msgid "<b>Fig # 36.</b> Entering the Animation module"
msgstr ""

#: en/drawing.html+html.body.p:22
msgid ""
"Now, let’s draw a guide line which will define the trajectory of the "
"butterfly, as defined in the script, using the <i>pencil</i> tool is already "
"selected:"
msgstr ""

#: en/drawing.html+html.body.center.p:29
msgid "<b>Fig # 37.</b> Drawing a guide line"
msgstr ""

#: en/drawing.html+html.body.p:32
msgid ""
"Note that, once drawn, you can adjust the path of your guide line, using the "
"<i>Nodes Selection</i> button located in the workspace toolbar:"
msgstr ""

#: en/drawing.html+html.body.center.p:39
msgid "<b>Fig # 38.</b> Activating Nodes Selection"
msgstr ""

#: en/drawing.html+html.body.p:43
msgid "When you select the line you’ve just drawn, it will look like this :"
msgstr ""

